revision.text:
The '''1938 [[Far Eastern Games]]''' were scheduled to be held in [[Osaka, Japan]], although they were cancelled due to the outbreak of [[Second Sino-Japanese War]].<ref>[http://fpok.upi.edu/the_origin_asiangames.htm Fan Hong, "Prologue: The Origin of the Asian Games," ''Sport, Nationalism and Orientalism''] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211171150/http://fpok.upi.edu/the_origin_asiangames.htm |date=February 11, 2012 }}</ref> After the cancellation of these 1938 Games the Far Eastern Games ceased to exist and they have been replaced by the [[Asian Games]] after World War II.
