{{Infobox venue | name = Antalya Expo Center | image = | image_caption = | nickname = | address = | location = [[Antalya]], [[Turkey]] | coordinates = {{coord|36.94049|N|30.81676|E|display=inline,title}} | type = | genre = Trade fair, indoor sports | built = | opened = 1999 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Antalya Fair Management and Investment Inc. (ANFAŞ) | construction_cost = | former_names = | seating_type = | seating_capacity = 3,800 | website = {{URL|http://www.anfas.com.tr/}} }}
'''Antalya Expo Center''' is an [[indoor arena]] in [[Antalya]], [[Turkey]]. The Expo Center was founded in 1999 by Antalya Fair Management and Investment Inc. It has a [[seating capacity]] for 3,800 people for sports events. It is located {{convert|5|km|mi|abbr=on}} north of the [[Antalya Airport]] and {{convert|11|km|mi|abbr=on}} northeast of the Antalya city.
The arena hosted some games of the first stages of [[Eurobasket 2001]] and the [[2010 World Weightlifting Championships]] on September 17–26.
