{{Infobox stadium | name = Ayr Ice Rink | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = 21 Beresford Terrace, [[Ayr]], [[Scotland]] | coordinates = {{coord |55|27|24|N|4|37|41|W|type:landmark_region:GB-SAY|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = 1938 | built = | opened = March 1939 <ref name=general>{{cite web|last=Stamp|first=Phil|title=Ay|url=http://www.azhockey.com/Ay.htm|work=a to z encyclopaedia of ice hockey|publisher=azhockey.com|accessdate=23 February 2012}}</ref> | renovated = | expanded = | closed = April 1972 <ref name="Closing date">{{cite web|last=Gordon|first=David|title=Frank Dempster (1937-2004)|url=http://www.manchesterphoenix.co.uk/news/s/13_frank_dempster_19372004|work=Manchester Phoenix Ice Hockey Club|publisher=Manchester Phoenix Ice Hockey Club|accessdate=23 February 2012}}</ref> | demolished = | owner = Ayr Ice Rink Ltd <ref name="Beresford Park">{{cite web|title=Single record details |url=http://195.153.34.9/onlinecatalogue/details.aspx?reference=RHP87632& |archive-url=https://archive.is/20121128201450/http://195.153.34.9/onlinecatalogue/details.aspx?reference=RHP87632& |dead-url=yes |archive-date=28 November 2012 |work=he National Archives of Scotland |publisher=he National Archives of Scotland |accessdate=23 February 2012 }}</ref> | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | estimated_cost = | suites = | architect = J & J A Carrick <ref name="J & JA Carrick">{{cite web|title=DSA Building/Design Report|url=http://www.scottisharchitects.org.uk/building_full.php?id=201625|work=Dictionary of Scottish Architects 1840-1980|publisher=Dictionary of Scottish Architects|accessdate=23 February 2012}}</ref> | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 4,616 (3,800 seated and 816 standing) <ref name=general /><ref name="Capacity">{{cite news|last=McInnes|first=Yonnie|title=Glen Henderson recalls his involvement with the Centrum and Ayr Ice Rink|url=http://www.ayrshirepost.net/lifestyle/lifestyle-news/2011/07/01/glen-henderson-recalls-his-involvement-with-the-centrum-and-ayr-ice-rink-102545-28959027/|accessdate=23 February 2012|newspaper=Ayrshire Post|date=Jul 1, 2011}}</ref> | record_attendance = | executive_suites = | dimensions = {{convert|200|x|100|ft|abbr=on}} <ref name=general /> | acreage = | tenants = }}
'''Ayr Ice Rink''' was an ice arena in [[Ayr]], [[Scotland]] that opened in 1939 and was used for [[ice skating]], [[ice hockey]] and [[curling]]. The rink was notable as being the home of professional ice hockey clubs [[Ayr Raiders]] and [[Ayr Bruins]].<ref name=Capacity />
The building was located at 21 Beresford Terrace on the former site of Beresford Park, home of [[Ayr Parkhouse F.C.|Ayr Parkhouse Football Club]].<ref name=Address>{{cite web|title=Site Record for Ayr, 21 Beresford Terrace, Ice Rink Details|url=http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/185716/details/ayr+21+beresford+terrace+ice+rink/|work=RCAHMS Website|publisher=The Royal Commission on the Ancient and Historical Monuments of Scotland|accessdate=23 February 2012}}</ref> Ayr Ice Rink Ltd purchased the land from [[London Midland and Scottish Railway]] in 1938 to build the rink.<ref name="Beresford Park" /><ref name="J & JA Carrick" />
The property was demolished in 1972 to make way for a [[Safeway (UK)|Safeway]] supermarket and today the site is occupied by two retail stores and carpark.<ref name="Closing date" />
A new ice rink was built at Limekiln Road on the site of the closed [[Ayr (Tams Brig) Greyhound Stadium]]<ref name="Ayr Curling Club">{{cite web|title=Location|url=http://www.ayrcurlingclub.co.uk/location/|work=Location|publisher=Ayr Curling Club|accessdate=23 February 2014}}</ref> and is owned by Ayr Curling Club. It is predominantly used for [[curling]] but [[figure skating]]<ref name="Ayr figure skating club">{{cite web|title=Introduction|url=http://www.afsc.org.uk/index.html|work=Ayr figure skating club|publisher=Ayr figure skating club|accessdate=23 February 2014}}</ref> and recreational [[ice hockey]]<ref name="Ayr Jets">{{cite web|title=About|url=http://www.ayrjets.co.uk/club_information.html|work=Ayr Jets|publisher=Ayr Jets|accessdate=23 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140601065156/http://ayrjets.co.uk/club_information.html|archive-date=2014-06-01|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> is also played there.
