===Best women's player=== *'''Decided by:''' Players and coaches
New award introduced in 2017.<ref name="women"/>
Fellow national team captains and coaches vote for who they want to be crowned best women's player of the year. BSWW reveal a shortlist of the three players with the most votes prior to the ceremony.{{ref|Note1|[Note]}} On the awards night, the winner of the award with the most votes of the three is revealed as the best women's player of the year. {| class="wikitable" |+Shortlists of three players with most votes ( {{Legend3|#ccffcc}} Award winner ): |- !Year !width=220|Player !width=190|Team |- |rowspan="4"|<center>'''2017'''<ref name="twentyseventeen"/></center> |-bgcolor=#ccffcc |{{flagicon|ENG}} '''Sarah Kempson''' || '''{{beachsoccerwomen|ENG}}''' |- |{{flagicon|NED}} Grytsje Van den Berg || {{beachsoccerwomen|Netherlands}} |- |{{flagicon|BRA}} Leticia Villar<sup>[[#1|1]]</sup> || {{flagicon|HUN}} Astra (club) |- !colspan=3| |- |rowspan="4"|<center>'''2018'''<ref name="twentyeighteen"/></center> |-bgcolor=#ccffcc |{{flagicon|RUS}} '''[[Marina Fedorova]] || '''{{flag|Russia}} |- |{{flagicon|ENG}} Molly Clark || {{beachsoccerwomen|ENG}} |- |{{flagicon|BRA}} Adriele Rocha<sup>[[#1|1]]</sup> || {{flagicon|POL}} Grembach Łódź (club) |} <div style="font-size: 85%;"> :1. Not involved with national team; clubs represented in BSWW competitions are therefore shown instead.
