{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox sportsperson | name = Bèto Adriana | birth_name = Eduardo Adriana | fullname = | nationality = | residence = | birth_date = {{birth date|1925|7|29|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Otrobanda]], [[Curaçao]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1997|4|10|1925|7|29|df=yes}} | death_place = | height = | weight = | country = | sport = [[Shooting sport|Sports shooting]], [[Olympic weightlifting|weightlifting]] | event = | medaltemplates = | show-medals = yes }}
'''Bèto Adriana''' (29 July 1925 &ndash; 10 April 1997) was a sportsman who represented the [[Netherlands Antilles]] at the Olympics. At the [[1960 Summer Olympics]] he competed in the [[Olympic weightlifting|weightlifting]] competition and at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]] he competed in the [[Shooting sport|sports shooting]].<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ad/beto-adriana-1.html |title=Bèto Adriana |accessdate=14 February 2016 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>
In weightlifting, he won three bronze medals at the [[Pan American Games]] from 1955 to 1963. He also finished fifth in the shot put competition at the [[1955 Pan American Games]].
