{{Infobox football biography | name = Reinhard Breinburg | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|5|2}} | birth_place = [[Purmerend]], [[Netherlands]] | currentclub = [[SV Dakota]] | clubnumber = | height = {{height|m=1.83}} | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Feyenoord]] | years1 = 2004–2010| clubs1 = [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]] | caps1 = 132| goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2010–2012| clubs2 = [[BVV Barendrecht|Barendrecht]] | caps2 = 40 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2012–2014| clubs3 = [[Quick Boys]] | caps3 = 41 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2014– | clubs4 = [[SV Dakota]] | caps4 = | goals4 = | nationalyears1 = 2011–2014 | nationalteam1 = [[Aruba national football team|Aruba]] | nationalcaps1 = 13 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 31 May 2015 | ntupdate = }}
'''Reinhard Richard Breinburg''' (born May 2, 1984 in [[Purmerend]], [[Netherlands]]) is a naturalized [[Aruba]]n [[association football|football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]], who plays for [[SV Dakota]].
==Club career== He played in the [[Feyenoord]] academy<ref>[https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/63889 REINHARD BREINBURG IN DE FEYENOORD KRANT] - Feyenoord {{nl|icon}}</ref> and joined [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]] in 2004. At Dordrecht, Breinburg was tested positive for use of an illegal substance.<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/reinhard-breinburg-positief-bevonden.htm Reinhard Breinburg positief bevonden] - Voetbal International {{nl|icon}}</ref> He was later suspended by the [[KNVB|Dutch FA]] for use of cannabis.<ref>[http://www.fcdordrecht.net/midden/actueel/archief/2005/20051212.htm Die affaires hebben me sterker gemaakt] - FC Dordrecht {{nl|icon}}</ref> In 2010, he joined amateur side [[BVV Barendrecht|Barendrecht]]<ref>[http://www.rijnmond.nl/nieuws/13681/Breinburg-vindt-onderdak-bij-Barendrecht Breinburg vindt onderdak bij Barendrecht] - Rijnmond {{nl|icon}}</ref> and he moved to [[Quick Boys]] two years later.<ref>[http://www.quickboys.nl/nieuws/3426/ Quick Boys strikt Reinhard Breinburg] - Quick Boys {{nl|icon}}</ref>
He left Quick Boys in 2014 and moved to Aruba to work on the island.<ref>[http://www.quickboys.nl/nieuws/4958/reinhard-breinburg-verlaat-sportpark-nieuw-zuid.html Reinhard Breinburg verlaat sportpark Nieuw Zuid] - Quick Boys {{nl|icon}}</ref>
==International career== Breinburg made his debut for [[Aruba national football team|Aruba]] in a December 2011 [[friendly match]] against [[Suriname national football team|Suriname]]<ref>[http://caribbeanfootballdatabase.com/aruba/players/reinhardbreinburg.html Intl career stats] - Caribbean Football Database</ref> and earned a total of 13 caps scoring no goals.
