{{about|the cricket ground|the road|Sydney Parade Avenue|the railway station|Sydney Parade railway station}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Sydney Parade | nickname = | country = Ireland | image = | location = [[Dublin]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] | establishment = 1897 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = | club1 = | date = 29 August | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/1314.html Ground profile }}
'''Sydney Parade''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Dublin]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1897, when Pembroke played Leicester Ivanhoe.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/1314_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Sydney Parade, Dublin|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref> In 1965, the ground hosted a [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match between [[Ireland cricket team|Ireland]] and [[Scotland cricket team|Scotland]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/1314_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Sydney Parade, Dublin|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref> which resulted in a Scottish victory by an innings and 22 runs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/27/27726.html|title=Ireland v Scotland, 1965|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref> In 1995, the ground hosted a [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day International]] between [[Ireland women's cricket team|Ireland women]] and the [[Netherlands women's cricket team|Netherlands women]]. The ground hosted further Women's One Day Internationals in 1996 when Ireland women played [[New Zealand women's cricket team|New Zealand women]], in 1997 when Ireland women played [[South Africa women's cricket team|South Africa women]], and in 2000 when Ireland women played [[Pakistan women's cricket team|Pakistan women]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/1314_wo.html|title=Women's One-Day International Matches played on Sydney Parade, Dublin|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref>
In club cricket, the ground is the home of [[Pembroke Cricket Club]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketleinster.ie/clubs/pembroke|title=Pembroke Cricket Club|publisher=www.cricketleinster.ie|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref>
