{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Zlatorog Arena | nickname = | image = [[File:Zlatorog Arena.jpg|250px|alt=]] | fullname = | location = [[Celje, Slovenia|Celje]], [[Slovenia]] | coordinates = {{coord|46.2477602|15.2708888|display=inline|type:landmark}} | broke_ground = 16 April 2003 | built = | opened = 2003 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = ZPO Celje d.o.o. | surface = [[parquet]] | construction_cost = | architect = Arhitekt ERNST d.o.o. | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenant = [[RK Celje]] | seating_capacity = 5,500 | dimensions = 40 x 20 m | scoreboard = }}
[[File:Slovenian fans.png|thumb|250px|Slovenian fans in the Zlatorog Arena]] '''Zlatorog Arena''' ({{lang-sl|Dvorana Zlatorog}}) is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Celje]], [[Slovenia]] and it was opened in December 2003. The arena has between 4,594 and 5,154 fixed seats, depending on the seating configuration, and also a standing area for approximately 500 people. It hosts the home games of [[RK Celje|Celje]] [[team handball]] club. Zlatorog Arena will host [[FIBA EuroBasket 2013 Group C|Group C]] of Preliminary round of [[FIBA EuroBasket 2013]]. Zlatorog means gold horn.
